WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.300
Michael owns
only 50 percent of Hotel 88.

00:00:03.300 --> 00:00:04.533
We share ownership of this?

00:00:04.533 --> 00:00:05.700
We want to buy your share.

00:00:05.700 --> 00:00:08.333
You're full of yourself!
Who do you think you are?

00:00:08.333 --> 00:00:09.767
- Martin, please.
- What?

00:00:09.767 --> 00:00:12.000
Can't you hear
what your sister is saying?

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:13.733
I'll talk to my siblings.

00:00:13.733 --> 00:00:16.267
I'll also talk to my siblings.

00:00:16.267 --> 00:00:18.533
This is not just any hotel.

00:00:18.533 --> 00:00:21.133
Don't sell Hotel 88.

00:00:21.133 --> 00:00:22.733
Because this is your home.

00:00:22.733 --> 00:00:24.967
And I want you to know...

00:00:25.533 --> 00:00:27.067
If we lose this hotel,

00:00:27.067 --> 00:00:29.200
we won't know what it is.

00:00:30.700 --> 00:00:32.033
I'm here.

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:35.033
Oh, I'm sorry, sir.

00:00:35.033 --> 00:00:36.367
We're not accepting guests yet

00:00:36.367 --> 00:00:38.433
because the hotel
is still closed.

00:00:38.433 --> 00:00:40.100
Yes, sir. My sister is right.

00:00:40.100 --> 00:00:41.533
We're really sorry.

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:45.167
But your website says
the hotel is now open.

00:00:45.167 --> 00:00:46.567
- Website?
- Huh?

00:00:46.567 --> 00:00:48.100
Do we have a website?

00:00:49.133 --> 00:00:52.433
All we have here
are spider webs, sir.

00:00:52.433 --> 00:00:54.600
If you want,
I'll refer you to another hotel.

00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:56.333
No. No need.

00:00:57.667 --> 00:00:59.200
He can stay here.

00:01:00.300 --> 00:01:02.033
Sir, our hotel's open.

00:01:02.033 --> 00:01:09.000
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:10.567 --> 00:01:12.633
Oh, I wasn't informed.
Since when?

00:01:12.633 --> 00:01:13.733
Now.

00:01:13.733 --> 00:01:19.533
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:01:19.533 --> 00:01:22.467
- Hello, Philippines!
- And hello, world!

00:01:22.467 --> 00:01:25.500
Alright! Welcome to Hotel 88!

00:01:25.500 --> 00:01:28.133
The hotel that was once evicted.

00:01:28.133 --> 00:01:29.400
Now, it's...

00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:31.100
- ...back!
- Back!

00:01:32.067 --> 00:01:33.267
Welcome, sir.

00:01:33.267 --> 00:01:34.400
Welcome.

00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:38.600
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:40.433
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

00:01:43.133 --> 00:01:44.533
[DOOR SQUEAKS SHUT]

00:01:44.533 --> 00:01:51.200
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:01:51.200 --> 00:01:52.633
[UNZIPPING]

00:01:52.633 --> 00:01:59.567
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:02:05.667 --> 00:02:11.867
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:11.867 --> 00:02:18.800
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:11.700 --> 00:03:18.633
[WATER SLOSHING, SPLASHING]

00:03:31.367 --> 00:03:36.767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:36.767 --> 00:03:43.733
[WIND CHIMES TINKLING]

00:03:43.733 --> 00:03:50.700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:03:51.667 --> 00:03:54.267
[FRED] Are you just
saying this after I told you

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:56.400
that Mike and I chose
to patch things up?

00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:59.867
Fred, I told you a long time ago
that I wanted to leave.

00:03:59.867 --> 00:04:02.300
It has nothing to do with that.

00:04:02.300 --> 00:04:04.200
And then,
where are you going?

00:04:05.633 --> 00:04:07.367
I applied as an immigrant.

00:04:07.367 --> 00:04:09.767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:09.767 --> 00:04:11.700
[SIGHS EXASPERATEDLY] What?!

00:04:12.700 --> 00:04:14.633
You really want
to leave me, don't you?

00:04:14.633 --> 00:04:16.867
I just want to live on my own.

00:04:16.867 --> 00:04:18.300
[FRED SCOFFS]

00:04:18.300 --> 00:04:20.300
- Please!
- Frida!

00:04:20.300 --> 00:04:22.533
We're too old for that, Frida!

00:04:22.533 --> 00:04:25.433
- Are you dead serious?!
- Exactly, Fred!

00:04:25.433 --> 00:04:26.833
Our kids are all grown up now!

00:04:26.833 --> 00:04:28.733
They can take care
of themselves.

00:04:28.767 --> 00:04:30.767
I'm just thinking
this is the perfect time.

00:04:30.767 --> 00:04:33.400
You are selfish!
You are being selfish!

00:04:34.967 --> 00:04:40.833
Fred, you know we've had
an unhappy marriage for years.

00:04:40.833 --> 00:04:42.633
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

00:04:42.633 --> 00:04:44.500
Mike's the reason, isn't he?

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:45.767
After all these years,

00:04:45.767 --> 00:04:47.800
- it's still Mike!
- No!

00:04:47.800 --> 00:04:49.433
Mike has nothing to do with...

00:04:49.433 --> 00:04:51.300
- what I want to happen...
- Oh, come on!

00:04:51.300 --> 00:04:53.400
...with my life!

00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:54.700
I give up!

00:04:55.733 --> 00:04:58.600
Whatever happened
between Mike and me

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:00.767
is in the past.

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:03.533
I just want to move on!

00:05:03.533 --> 00:05:07.333
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

00:05:07.333 --> 00:05:09.733
[SNIFFLES, BREATHES SHAKILY]

00:05:09.733 --> 00:05:12.600
[SNIFFLING, SOBBING]

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:15.733
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:05:15.733 --> 00:05:22.700
[MUSIC BECOMES UNSETTLING]

00:05:26.967 --> 00:05:31.767
[WATER SLOSHING]

00:05:31.767 --> 00:05:38.733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:05:52.467 --> 00:05:58.800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:01.600
- [CELLPHONE RINGING]
- [TAPPING]

00:06:04.667 --> 00:06:05.800
Hello?

00:06:07.767 --> 00:06:09.967
Have you read my e-mails?

00:06:13.067 --> 00:06:15.367
[SIGHS] So, I'm right?

00:06:15.367 --> 00:06:19.100
- [UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SIGHS DEEPLY]

00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:21.800
These are the things that need
to be fixed at the hotel.

00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:24.067
That's just my estimate, but...

00:06:25.367 --> 00:06:26.933
It's not okay, is it?

00:06:28.833 --> 00:06:30.600
[SIGHS] Alright.

00:06:30.600 --> 00:06:32.633
Thank you again
for the consultation, bro.

00:06:32.633 --> 00:06:36.033
I'll let you know
if we need a new accountant.

00:06:36.033 --> 00:06:37.733
Okay. Thanks again.

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:41.533
- [SIGHS]
- [CELLPHONE THUDS]

00:06:41.567 --> 00:06:46.833
- [UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SIGHS EXASPERATEDLY]

00:06:46.833 --> 00:06:49.167
- [WAVES CRASHING]
- [WIND BLOWING]

00:06:49.167 --> 00:06:56.100
- [OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BIRDS CHIRPING]

00:07:11.133 --> 00:07:18.033
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:07:31.633 --> 00:07:38.600
- [OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WIND CHIMES TINKLING]

00:07:43.800 --> 00:07:47.533
[CELLPHONE BUZZING]

00:07:47.567 --> 00:07:48.600
Hello?

00:07:49.900 --> 00:07:52.500
Most probably,
it's in Mike's room.

00:07:52.500 --> 00:07:54.467
I just don't know
where exactly it is.

00:07:54.467 --> 00:07:59.467
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:07:59.467 --> 00:08:01.467
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

00:08:01.467 --> 00:08:05.967
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:08:05.967 --> 00:08:07.667
[DOOR CREAKS SHUT]

00:08:07.667 --> 00:08:14.633
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:08:19.533 --> 00:08:21.233
[DOORKNOB CLANKING]

00:08:21.267 --> 00:08:24.800
[MUSIC SWELLS]

00:08:24.800 --> 00:08:30.600
[DOORKNOB RATTLING, CLICKING]

00:08:30.600 --> 00:08:31.800
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:33.000
[KIKO] Sir.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:34.233
[DOOR CLICKS SHUT]

00:08:34.233 --> 00:08:39.100
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:39.100 --> 00:08:43.500
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

00:08:45.567 --> 00:08:47.567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:47.567 --> 00:08:48.967
Do you need anything?

00:08:49.533 --> 00:08:50.733
Ah, nothing.

00:08:50.733 --> 00:08:51.733
Nothing.

00:08:51.733 --> 00:08:53.200
Um...

00:08:53.200 --> 00:08:57.233
I was just looking at the places
here in the hotel because...

00:08:57.267 --> 00:08:59.267
this is different from the
places I've vacationed at.

00:09:00.333 --> 00:09:01.433
Ah.

00:09:01.433 --> 00:09:03.200
Well, this area is off-limits.

00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:04.333
This is private.

00:09:04.333 --> 00:09:05.400
Let's stay here instead.

00:09:06.667 --> 00:09:07.733
Ah, really?

00:09:09.333 --> 00:09:10.400
This is off-limits?

00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:12.367
Why?

00:09:13.033 --> 00:09:14.733
Is this the owners' room?

00:09:14.733 --> 00:09:18.367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:18.367 --> 00:09:19.400
[CHUCKLES SLIGHTLY]

00:09:20.300 --> 00:09:22.767
You know what,
just give me a tour.

00:09:22.767 --> 00:09:25.167
So I'll know which areas here
are off-limits and which aren't.

00:09:26.633 --> 00:09:28.033
Okay.

00:09:28.067 --> 00:09:29.367
Alright, let's go.

00:09:29.367 --> 00:09:30.400
This way, sir.

00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:35.800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:09:35.800 --> 00:09:37.600
[RAPHIE] We only have one guest,

00:09:37.600 --> 00:09:39.333
and you're still
overthinking like that?

00:09:39.733 --> 00:09:41.467
I wouldn't overthink it

00:09:41.467 --> 00:09:44.167
if he wasn't trying
to open Papa's room.

00:09:44.167 --> 00:09:45.533
Maybe he just got lost?

00:09:46.400 --> 00:09:48.633
Maybe there was traffic
on his way back to his room,

00:09:48.633 --> 00:09:50.767
so he was just too
embarrassed to admit it.

00:09:50.767 --> 00:09:53.667
Oh my god, Raphie! What?
Are you joking again?

00:09:53.667 --> 00:09:55.267
Okay, what if...

00:09:55.633 --> 00:09:57.233
What if he has other plans?

00:09:57.800 --> 00:09:59.833
What if he's a thief?

00:09:59.833 --> 00:10:05.200
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:10:05.233 --> 00:10:06.600
Hey, Raphie.

00:10:07.600 --> 00:10:09.233
- Are you okay?
- Huh?

00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:11.467
I just have a feeling.

00:10:11.467 --> 00:10:12.433
[KIKO] Really?

00:10:12.867 --> 00:10:13.833
What is it?

00:10:14.367 --> 00:10:15.733
Do you believe me now?

00:10:17.133 --> 00:10:18.533
I can feel it now.

00:10:18.533 --> 00:10:22.367
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:10:22.367 --> 00:10:24.367
[WIND CHIMES TINKLING]

00:10:24.367 --> 00:10:28.067
[WIND BLOWING]

00:10:28.733 --> 00:10:31.200
[WIND CHIME TINKLING DISTANTLY]

00:10:31.200 --> 00:10:38.167
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:10:39.767 --> 00:10:40.833
Leon?

00:10:40.833 --> 00:10:45.133
[FOOTSTEPS]

00:10:51.900 --> 00:10:53.133
[LUNA] Jade?

00:10:53.133 --> 00:10:59.867
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:11:02.400 --> 00:11:03.633
Jade?

00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:06.733
Justin?

00:11:12.167 --> 00:11:15.933
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:11:15.933 --> 00:11:17.300
Who is that?

00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:25.867
[CHIMES]

00:11:27.767 --> 00:11:28.867
[GASPS]

00:11:30.233 --> 00:11:31.400
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

00:11:31.400 --> 00:11:32.467
Mom!

00:11:32.467 --> 00:11:39.400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:40.567 --> 00:11:42.533
[RAPHIE] I have a feeling...

00:11:42.833 --> 00:11:44.400
that something's coming.

00:11:45.267 --> 00:11:46.667
Which one?

00:11:46.667 --> 00:11:50.200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:50.200 --> 00:11:51.800
[RAPHIE] It's coming.

00:11:52.833 --> 00:11:54.800
The festival is coming up!

00:11:55.833 --> 00:11:57.833
- Oh my god.
- The festival's coming up!

00:11:57.833 --> 00:11:59.433
I thought it was something else!

00:11:59.433 --> 00:12:01.833
Isn't that a big deal
to you, Kiko?

00:12:01.833 --> 00:12:03.500
When there's a festival,
there are many tourists.

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:05.800
When there are many tourists,
there's a lot of bookings!

00:12:06.200 --> 00:12:07.900
[STUTTERS] Booking of guests!

00:12:07.900 --> 00:12:10.500
Many guests will
book at our hotel.

00:12:10.500 --> 00:12:12.667
Don't you want a lot of guests
to check-in at the hotel?

00:12:12.667 --> 00:12:14.267
So just do your job properly

00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:16.667
because that's for
our future guests.

00:12:23.367 --> 00:12:24.633
Take this.

00:12:25.433 --> 00:12:27.400
- [PILLS RATTLING]
- It'll help you fall asleep.

00:12:29.667 --> 00:12:30.800
That's a strong dosage.

00:12:31.900 --> 00:12:33.533
Thank you, dear.

00:12:36.667 --> 00:12:38.800
You know, ever since Dad died...

00:12:39.833 --> 00:12:41.800
I couldn't sleep either.

00:12:42.833 --> 00:12:45.800
It was all so sudden.

00:12:46.433 --> 00:12:48.400
I'm still in shock.

00:12:48.867 --> 00:12:51.433
It hurts too much, Luna.

00:12:52.467 --> 00:12:53.867
[SNIFFLES]

00:12:53.867 --> 00:12:56.833
I know that I shouldn't be
thinking about this,

00:12:56.833 --> 00:12:59.433
that I should be
thinking about you.

00:12:59.433 --> 00:13:01.400
[FRIDA] About you, my children.

00:13:01.700 --> 00:13:02.800
No, Mom.

00:13:04.433 --> 00:13:05.833
Grieve.

00:13:05.833 --> 00:13:08.433
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:08.433 --> 00:13:10.600
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

00:13:10.600 --> 00:13:13.333
I'll stay here until
you fall asleep.

00:13:16.433 --> 00:13:18.800
Do you know what's
on my mind, Mom?

00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:23.867
What could they really
have fought about?

00:13:23.867 --> 00:13:25.867
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:13:25.867 --> 00:13:27.867
[FREDERICO] Was Mike
responsible for this?

00:13:27.867 --> 00:13:29.867
Mike is still the reason.

00:13:29.867 --> 00:13:31.000
After all these years,

00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:33.367
- it's still Mike!
- Wait, no!

00:13:33.367 --> 00:13:39.933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:39.933 --> 00:13:42.400
[LUNA] How did they get
to that point?

00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:46.333
Of killing.

00:13:49.433 --> 00:13:52.800
Isn't it connected to
their previous fight before?

00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:55.967
They hadn't spoken for
more than 10 years.

00:13:57.033 --> 00:13:59.467
That means it runs deep,
doesn't it?

00:13:59.467 --> 00:14:01.867
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:14:01.867 --> 00:14:04.833
Luna, let's not think
about those things.

00:14:07.867 --> 00:14:09.433
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:13.567
Whatever the reason was...

00:14:13.933 --> 00:14:17.467
it mattered so much that
they'd kill over it.

00:14:17.467 --> 00:14:24.400
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:30.300 --> 00:14:31.167
[GIO] Bro.

00:14:31.167 --> 00:14:32.867
You just got
your commission, right?

00:14:32.867 --> 00:14:34.533
Can you lend me some cash?

00:14:36.367 --> 00:14:37.633
[MAN]
You're borrowing money again?

00:14:38.633 --> 00:14:41.433
You know I won't ask you
if it isn't important.

00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:46.233
I just need to pay Bok
so he'd leave me alone.

00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:50.533
Bok? Don't you owe him
almost two million pesos?

00:14:52.767 --> 00:14:53.867
Yes, that's why...

00:14:55.300 --> 00:14:56.533
I'm asking for your help.

00:14:57.433 --> 00:14:59.833
It doesn't have to be full.
Just half will do.

00:14:59.833 --> 00:15:02.767
I'm also expecting money
from my father.

00:15:03.633 --> 00:15:06.200
As soon as I get it,
I'll pay you.

00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:07.467
With interest.

00:15:07.733 --> 00:15:10.767
Bro, wherever you are,
just stay there for now.

00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:13.967
Why?

00:15:13.967 --> 00:15:17.567
Just lay low while you still
don't have the money to pay Bo.

00:15:17.567 --> 00:15:18.867
Good luck.

00:15:20.333 --> 00:15:21.300
Gio.

00:15:22.233 --> 00:15:23.900
I'll call you later, bro.

00:15:29.233 --> 00:15:30.300
What?

00:15:30.867 --> 00:15:32.900
Martin's calling
for a family meeting.

00:15:34.867 --> 00:15:36.300
"Family meeting?"

00:15:36.300 --> 00:15:37.933
How formal.
Fine, I'll be there.

00:15:38.867 --> 00:15:41.433
Martin and his brothers
aren't selling.

00:15:43.867 --> 00:15:45.933
Aren't they just waiting
for us to raise our offer?

00:15:47.533 --> 00:15:48.800
As of the moment,

00:15:49.467 --> 00:15:53.400
we need to accept the fact
that we are co-owners.

00:15:53.400 --> 00:15:55.300
And we have to work with them?

00:15:55.300 --> 00:15:57.500
To reopen the hotel.

00:15:57.500 --> 00:15:59.467
That's our best option
right now.

00:15:59.467 --> 00:16:00.833
And we will cooperate.

00:16:02.300 --> 00:16:03.367
No!

00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:06.267
We can manage it without them.

00:16:06.267 --> 00:16:07.267
[MARTIN] Yes.

00:16:07.267 --> 00:16:10.733
But Luna won't just
let us call the shots.

00:16:11.567 --> 00:16:14.600
As long as the division
of work is clear,

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:15.833
I'm fine with that.

00:16:16.800 --> 00:16:19.233
It might even benefit us
to work with them.

00:16:19.667 --> 00:16:21.700
Why would I want to work
with that Luna,

00:16:23.567 --> 00:16:25.367
let alone the rest of
her siblings?

00:16:26.533 --> 00:16:29.367
We have no choice.
It's official.

00:16:29.367 --> 00:16:30.900
We have equal shares.

00:16:31.667 --> 00:16:33.633
Do what you want!
I just need my money!

00:16:34.867 --> 00:16:36.567
Why am I not surprised?

00:16:36.567 --> 00:16:41.767
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:42.833
Can I...

00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:45.600
...have the guest's deposit?

00:16:48.300 --> 00:16:49.333
Huh?

00:16:49.767 --> 00:16:51.433
What, you already want
an advance?

00:16:52.600 --> 00:16:55.267
You know I badly need it
right now, don't you?

00:16:55.267 --> 00:16:59.000
Yes, but we also need the money
to keep the hotel running.

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:00.733
The guest's payment
isn't even enough

00:17:00.733 --> 00:17:01.867
to cover our expenses.

00:17:03.367 --> 00:17:05.467
I won't gain anything
from this meeting.

00:17:05.467 --> 00:17:10.733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:17:10.733 --> 00:17:12.900
You heard him loud and clear.
We can do what we want.

00:17:13.633 --> 00:17:15.933
He didn't oppose us
working with the Almazans.

00:17:21.067 --> 00:17:24.567
Leon, can I just work from home?

00:17:25.533 --> 00:17:26.467
We'll see.

00:17:27.600 --> 00:17:30.600
But when we're there, please...

00:17:31.400 --> 00:17:33.967
Let's be civil with them.

00:17:35.900 --> 00:17:40.367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:40.367 --> 00:17:41.300
What?

00:17:42.433 --> 00:17:43.900
Why are you looking at me?

00:17:45.467 --> 00:17:47.967
I'm saying this to everyone.

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:49.067
[SCOFFS]

00:17:50.067 --> 00:17:51.767
You're right, Leon.

00:17:52.833 --> 00:17:54.533
Be civil.

00:17:54.533 --> 00:17:55.767
[JUSTIN SCOFFS]

00:17:56.700 --> 00:17:57.833
Civil?

00:17:58.600 --> 00:18:01.500
We don't want to
make things worse, do we?

00:18:04.600 --> 00:18:06.800
You guys are good kids.

00:18:06.800 --> 00:18:07.867
You, Leon...

00:18:09.033 --> 00:18:10.033
Luna...

00:18:11.067 --> 00:18:12.367
Justin...

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:14.033
Jade.

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:17.533
Maintain civility.

00:18:23.467 --> 00:18:30.400
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

00:18:32.767 --> 00:18:35.833
- Grandma?
- Hey, my dear grandson!

00:18:35.833 --> 00:18:38.067
I'm glad you picked up.

00:18:38.067 --> 00:18:39.667
I thought you had
forgotten about me.

00:18:40.600 --> 00:18:41.867
Sorry, Grandma.

00:18:41.867 --> 00:18:44.767
I missed your message last night
because I fell asleep early.

00:18:45.800 --> 00:18:47.067
Have you taken your meds?

00:18:47.867 --> 00:18:50.133
Of course. How could I forget?

00:18:50.133 --> 00:18:54.700
Our neighbor, Preska,
kept coming here

00:18:54.700 --> 00:18:57.100
to remind me to take
my meds

00:18:57.133 --> 00:18:58.567
and check my blood pressure.

00:18:58.567 --> 00:18:59.667
She's so fussy!

00:19:00.600 --> 00:19:03.067
Well, I told her
to look after you.

00:19:03.067 --> 00:19:05.567
I can take care of myself.

00:19:05.567 --> 00:19:07.133
How about you?
How are you?

00:19:09.933 --> 00:19:11.100
I'm fine, Grandma.

00:19:12.033 --> 00:19:14.467
We're actually attending
to our first guest.

00:19:14.467 --> 00:19:15.967
Oh!

00:19:15.967 --> 00:19:18.133
You reopened the hotel?

00:19:18.133 --> 00:19:22.133
That's great news! Really?!

00:19:22.133 --> 00:19:23.600
It's just one person, Grandma.

00:19:23.600 --> 00:19:29.600
I'm sure you'll have
a fully-booked hotel in no tim!

00:19:29.633 --> 00:19:31.667
Oh, I'm so happy for you!

00:19:31.667 --> 00:19:35.567
But I also miss you so bad.

00:19:35.567 --> 00:19:37.700
When are you coming home?

00:19:38.767 --> 00:19:42.633
Don't worry. When I earn enough
I'll go home right away.

00:19:43.467 --> 00:19:44.700
That's a promise.

00:19:45.567 --> 00:19:48.000
Okay. Take care, alright?

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:54.900
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:20:00.900 --> 00:20:02.600
What do you mean
we don't have money?

00:20:02.633 --> 00:20:05.200
- Good day, sir.
- You're not bankrupt.

00:20:05.200 --> 00:20:06.967
But the cash equivalents
of your business

00:20:06.967 --> 00:20:10.200
is only enough to keep the
hotel running for six months.

00:20:10.200 --> 00:20:12.700
Six months?
Hold on, Attorney.

00:20:13.333 --> 00:20:15.400
I read the partnership contract.
It's right here.

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:20.200
The money Uncle Fred invested is
more than enough for six months.

00:20:21.133 --> 00:20:22.300
[ATTORNEY] Yes.

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:24.167
The agreement states

00:20:24.167 --> 00:20:27.700
that Mr. Almazan contributed
50 million in cash...

00:20:28.467 --> 00:20:32.067
...on behalf and in trust
for his four children.

00:20:32.067 --> 00:20:33.800
So, where is the 50 million?

00:20:34.900 --> 00:20:36.133
I don't know.

00:20:36.167 --> 00:20:37.900
It was just on paper.

00:20:39.733 --> 00:20:41.300
Don't we have
any acknowledgment receipt,

00:20:41.300 --> 00:20:44.067
deposit slip,
or anything that can prove

00:20:44.067 --> 00:20:45.867
that Uncle Fred invested
that money?

00:20:47.100 --> 00:20:48.767
What does that mean, Attorney?

00:20:49.133 --> 00:20:54.867
Papa agreed to give the Almazans
a share of this hotel for free?

00:20:55.433 --> 00:20:59.333
[ATTORNEY] Look, I'm just
telling you what I know.

00:21:00.933 --> 00:21:02.867
The 50 million
is nowhere to be found

00:21:02.867 --> 00:21:06.433
and the hotel owes the bank
money that you need to pay.

00:21:09.767 --> 00:21:11.767
We have to pay off
the hotel's debts?

00:21:16.100 --> 00:21:18.500
Yes. And if you fail to do so...

00:21:22.800 --> 00:21:24.833
We'll lose the hotel.

00:21:24.833 --> 00:21:31.400
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:43.000
[RAPHIE]
Here's your order, sir.

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:48.233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:21:48.233 --> 00:21:50.300
[GIO] Our father
really is
the best, huh?

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:52.133
He made us inherit a hotel
with a mountain of problems!

00:21:52.133 --> 00:21:55.133
Blaming Papa
won't do us any good.

00:21:55.133 --> 00:21:58.833
What we should focus on
is generating money

00:21:58.833 --> 00:22:00.933
so we don't lose the hotel
in six months.

00:22:01.433 --> 00:22:03.033
Don't you think it's odd?

00:22:04.133 --> 00:22:07.133
If Papa agreed to share
the hotel with Uncle Fred,

00:22:07.133 --> 00:22:09.433
it would mean he's
a generous friend.

00:22:09.433 --> 00:22:11.067
So what?

00:22:11.067 --> 00:22:13.033
Why would he shoot Uncle Fred

00:22:13.033 --> 00:22:15.000
if he agreed to share the hotel
in the first place?

00:22:16.867 --> 00:22:20.100
Maybe Uncle Fred triggered him
by asking for a bigger share.

00:22:20.100 --> 00:22:22.133
They might've been drunk
when they made that agreement.

00:22:22.600 --> 00:22:25.000
I don't know what to think.

00:22:25.833 --> 00:22:27.967
Only Papa and Uncle Fred
could answer that.

00:22:27.967 --> 00:22:29.433
but they're gone.

00:22:29.433 --> 00:22:30.500
So, if I were you,

00:22:30.500 --> 00:22:33.200
I'd just focus on
making the hotel profitable.

00:22:33.200 --> 00:22:40.067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:22:40.900 --> 00:22:44.433
Our guest does look suspicious.

00:22:45.300 --> 00:22:47.033
He almost went
into Sir Mike's room

00:22:47.033 --> 00:22:50.000
and now he's listening in
on the brothers' conversation.

00:22:50.033 --> 00:22:51.967
I believe Kiko now.

00:22:56.300 --> 00:22:57.600
What are we going to do?

00:22:57.600 --> 00:22:59.467
For now, we stay put.

00:23:01.000 --> 00:23:02.967
I thought you believed Kiko.

00:23:03.867 --> 00:23:07.533
Yeah, but he hasn't done
anything to harm us.

00:23:07.533 --> 00:23:14.433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:23:15.433 --> 00:23:16.833
I'd better go back to work.

00:23:25.733 --> 00:23:27.000
We also need to hire
additional staff.

00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:30.233
Monette and Raphie
can't do all the work here.

00:23:30.233 --> 00:23:31.933
[MARTIN] We'll get there.

00:23:32.933 --> 00:23:36.233
They can't make decisions
without consulting us.

00:23:36.233 --> 00:23:37.933
What do they think of us?

00:23:37.933 --> 00:23:44.833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:52.533
You accepted a guest
and you didn't tell us?

00:23:52.533 --> 00:23:54.133
It was all so sudden.

00:23:54.133 --> 00:23:55.867
But we did inform you.

00:23:56.433 --> 00:23:58.600
Just admit you want this hotel
all for yourselves.

00:23:59.933 --> 00:24:01.933
You should thank us
for accepting guests.

00:24:01.933 --> 00:24:04.867
That way, we can earn money
to pay off this hotel's debts.

00:24:07.933 --> 00:24:10.400
[MARTIN] A loan was taken out
under the hotel's name.

00:24:11.600 --> 00:24:14.067
The hotel was signed off
as collateral.

00:24:15.033 --> 00:24:17.533
Why don't you use Dad's
contribution to pay it off?

00:24:17.533 --> 00:24:19.567
Your Dad didn't
contribute a penny!

00:24:20.600 --> 00:24:23.333
Our attorney checked everything.
We received nothing.

00:24:24.600 --> 00:24:26.200
That's a lie.

00:24:26.200 --> 00:24:28.167
Where did you put
the money, huh?

00:24:28.200 --> 00:24:31.067
We wouldn't be in debt
if we have the 50 million.

00:24:31.900 --> 00:24:33.367
The agreement shouldn't be valid

00:24:33.367 --> 00:24:35.933
because your father
didn't do his end of the deal.

00:24:35.933 --> 00:24:37.500
We don't even know
he convinced Papa

00:24:37.500 --> 00:24:39.500
to give him shares without
getting anything in return.

00:24:39.500 --> 00:24:42.367
For sure Uncle Mike
had a reason to agree.

00:24:43.633 --> 00:24:47.600
No matter what you say,
the agreement is legal.

00:24:47.600 --> 00:24:49.600
Why don't we focus
on the hotel?

00:24:49.600 --> 00:24:52.267
Our funds are only good
for six months.

00:24:52.267 --> 00:24:54.333
And if we don't make this
hotel operational,

00:24:54.333 --> 00:24:55.633
we'd end up with nothing.

00:24:55.633 --> 00:24:58.100
We won't be able
to pay the bank.

00:24:58.100 --> 00:25:00.600
Okay, fine!
Let's reopen the hotel.

00:25:00.600 --> 00:25:03.200
We'll use whatever money
it'll make to pay the bank.

00:25:04.200 --> 00:25:05.933
It's not going to be that easy.

00:25:07.233 --> 00:25:10.067
What we need is structure.

00:25:11.067 --> 00:25:15.333
We need a general manager
to lead this hotel's operations.

00:25:16.400 --> 00:25:19.000
And I think that's me.

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:20.067
[LUNA LAUGHS IN DISDAIN]

00:25:20.067 --> 00:25:21.300
Oh, no, no, no, no.

00:25:21.300 --> 00:25:23.933
You are not the only one who
knows how to run a business.

00:25:23.933 --> 00:25:25.000
[JADE] Right.

00:25:25.000 --> 00:25:27.667
You can do it.
Right, Leon?

00:25:27.667 --> 00:25:29.300
I can do it!

00:25:29.533 --> 00:25:32.567
You already kept your shares.
Leave the leadership to us.

00:25:34.100 --> 00:25:35.900
We want things to be fair?

00:25:38.233 --> 00:25:39.633
Let's vote on it.

00:25:39.633 --> 00:25:46.533
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:26:01.300 --> 00:26:03.000
There's four of them
and only three of us.

00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:04.300
Leon will vote for me.

00:26:04.300 --> 00:26:05.500
What confidence you have.

00:26:05.500 --> 00:26:08.100
Martin is your best friend,
but I am your sister.

00:26:08.100 --> 00:26:10.533
- I have your vote, right?
- Even if you're his friend,

00:26:10.567 --> 00:26:12.667
you're going against
his sister!

00:26:12.667 --> 00:26:17.033
Your vote will determine who
will be the general manager

00:26:17.033 --> 00:26:18.500
of Hotel 88.

00:26:18.500 --> 00:26:21.033
Bok, you're crazy!
I told you I pay, didn't I?!

00:26:21.033 --> 00:26:23.133
Don't wait until I give
your grandma another visit.

00:26:23.133 --> 00:26:25.167
If only I could
revoke their shares.

00:26:25.167 --> 00:26:28.100
Have they done any misconduct
that goes against the agreement?

00:26:28.100 --> 00:26:32.667
Just one mistake, and they can
legally take this away from us.

00:26:32.667 --> 00:26:35.400
- This looks bad.
- If you trust each other,

00:26:35.400 --> 00:26:36.733
would you kill each other?

00:26:36.733 --> 00:26:38.967
Are you saying
someone else killed them?

00:26:39.367 --> 00:26:40.367
No!

00:26:40.367 --> 00:26:42.300
- Aah!
- Watch out!

00:26:42.333 --> 00:26:44.567
You almost broke my earring!

00:26:45.633 --> 00:26:47.033
I know that earring.